1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:01,610
Animation is information.

2
00:00:01,880 --> 00:00:04,600
It shows progress, confirms an outcome,

3
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:06,950
or explains where focus moved.

4
00:00:07,250 --> 00:00:10,200
But reduced-motion implementations often
delete the animation,

5
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:12,520
and the information with it.

6
00:00:12,810 --> 00:00:17,300
StillMeaning asks one question:
what disappears when motion disappears?

7
00:00:17,590 --> 00:00:20,210
Then it reduces the motion,
not the meaning.

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:25,360
This continuous shimmer says
the upload is still active.

9
00:00:25,690 --> 00:00:28,880
If we merely turn it off,
the bar becomes static.

10
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:33,350
Is it progressing or stalled,
and what is the exact value?

11
00:00:33,620 --> 00:00:37,200
StillMeaning traces that ambiguity,
then replaces the moving cue

12
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,850
with visible status text,

13
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:48,800
a numeric value,
and real progress-bar semantics.

14
00:00:55,180 --> 00:01:00,640
Here, scale, rotation, and path drawing
are the success message.

15
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:04,330
Turning them off leaves only
an unlabeled icon.

16
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:07,800
StillMeaning makes the result persistent
and explicit with Changes saved text,

17
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:10,760
synchronization detail, and a polite
status announcement,

18
00:01:11,050 --> 00:01:17,900
without relying on motion or color alone.

19
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:25,360
This large slide communicates movement
into a deeper level.

20
00:01:25,620 --> 00:01:29,900
Removing it without a replacement creates
an unexplained content swap

21
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:32,620
and leaves keyboard focus behind.

22
00:01:32,990 --> 00:01:35,700
StillMeaning adds explicit hierarchy,
names the destination,

23
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:38,420
and moves focus logically while replacing
the travel with only a short fade.

24
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,000
StillMeaning does not stop at advice.

25
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:46,500
It generates an inspectable implementation
and shows the exact before-and-after diff,

26
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:50,500
explains the transformation,
and lets a developer copy the result.

27
00:01:50,500 --> 00:01:58,040
Generated code is displayed as untrusted text
and is never executed inside the workbench.

28
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,600
GPT-5.6 performs the core reasoning.

29
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:04,200
It identifies each motion-carried signal
and predicts what becomes lost or ambiguous,

30
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:07,500
selects replacement cues, generates code,

31
00:02:07,780 --> 00:02:09,290
and links each cue to structured
validation evidence.

32
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:11,050
The server uses strict schema validation
and bounded input,

33
00:02:11,050 --> 00:02:12,630
a timeout, and a server-only key.

34
00:02:12,630 --> 00:02:14,900
Provenance always distinguishes live GPT-5.6

35
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:17,240
from the clearly labeled demo fallback
shown here.

36
00:02:17,530 --> 00:02:18,950
Codex helped audit, design, implement, test,

37
00:02:18,950 --> 00:02:20,460
debug, deploy, and document the project
in one primary development session.

38
00:02:20,460 --> 00:02:21,900
StillMeaning: reduce motion, not meaning.
